    {
      "id": "d338915899f4e81cf5fdf9438dbdbea408432be8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 212,
        "name": "Alexander Boyko",
        "email": "alexander.boyko@hpe.com",
        "username": "aboyko"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-27 07:08:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAlex, the problem with per export commited with http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5143 still exist. And it will update only obd commited, but server put per export commited to reply without current fix. So, both patches are needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7b4d761b7f65227a6054e7ee2de8ab209788d812",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-27 07:12:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nhmm, but if the client keeps to open/close, then it will be getting new own transno?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bd8927835aed90b77aed4ea302b1a61f69a67c91",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 212,
        "name": "Alexander Boyko",
        "email": "alexander.boyko@hpe.com",
        "username": "aboyko"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-27 07:18:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIf Lustre use noatime/relatime and do only ls -laR, for example, client will get zero commited transno and modification activity from another client does not change this zero value.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b016f465a259e72f369823d8d032a9e2b9706031",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-27 07:20:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nare you saying the client opened 200K files, then closed them and now doing only ls/stat?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bc8269306ee0df4853894f5ea50b8098b1ded00a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 212,
        "name": "Alexander Boyko",
        "email": "alexander.boyko@hpe.com",
        "username": "aboyko"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-27 07:28:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPls, look at issue description.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "78042dc6284666ccd1f7814ebb87c772e85f7505",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-27 07:28:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAlex,\n\nclient have open N directories and do stat for each file in it. In that case open / close in replay queue as none updates from a server. Issuing a touch $mnt2/some_file don't flush a replay queue on affected client as none last commited updates are send. \nthat is example - first client (issued a touch) have a last_commited updates, but second (with ls -lR) don't have updates and don't able to flush own replay queue.\n\n00010000:00000040:3.0:1369489394.318119:0:8210:0:(ldlm_lib.c:2541:target_committed_to_req()) last_committed 47244642357, transno 47244642363, xid 1436013481180501\n00000100:00100000:3.0:1369489394.318244:0:8210:0:00010000:00000040:1.0:1369489395.311623:0:8438:0:(ldlm_lib.c:2541:target_committed_to_req()) last_committed 0, transno 0, xid 1436013481180503",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
